{"id":4851,"date":"2022-06-22T19:48:56","date_gmt":"2022-06-22T19:48:56","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/zerocarbonhousebirmingham.org.uk\/?p=4851"},"modified":"2022-06-22T20:52:19","modified_gmt":"2022-06-22T20:52:19","slug":"open-day","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/zerocarbonhousebirmingham.org.uk\/open-day\/","title":{"rendered":"RETROFIT REIMAGINED"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-1 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:100%\"><\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>All are warmly invited to <a href=\"https:\/\/civicsquare.notion.site\/Retrofit-Reimagined-9eb1d36585824faa89486ebfa12d1e86\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/civicsquare.notion.site\/Retrofit-Reimagined-9eb1d36585824faa89486ebfa12d1e86\">RETROFIT REIMAGINED<\/a> mini-festival in Birmingham, 13-16 July!&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>zero carbon house is collaborating with: <a href=\"https:\/\/civicsquare.cc\/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/civicsquare.cc\/\">Civic Square<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/neweconomics.org\/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/neweconomics.org\/\">New Economics Foundation<\/a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/darkmatterlabs.org\/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/darkmatterlabs.org\/\">Dark Matter Labs<\/a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/www.architectscan.org\/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/www.architectscan.org\/\">Architects Climate Action Network ACAN&nbsp;<\/a> and a galaxy of Retrofit stars to explore the question:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow\"><p><strong>\u201cWhat if the climate transition and retrofit of our homes and streets were designed, owned and governed by the people who live there?\u201d&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p><\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>Retrofitting means proper insulation to walls, floors, roofs; new windows and doors; ventilation with heat recovery, heat pumps, solar panels etc. The different measures will vary as every house is different.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>zero carbon house is proud to be UK\u2019s first zero carbon retrofit, now 13 years old. &nbsp;But by now there should be millions of others too\u2026.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Our old leaky homes seem to be the forgotten Cinderella, haemorrhaging massive amounts of heat. It\u2019s really important these homes &#8211; and the people who live in them &#8211;&nbsp;are not left behind.&nbsp;&nbsp;People\u2019s physical and mental health is badly affected by poor housing with mould, damp, condensation &#8211; and massive fuel bills.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Retrofitting our old homes properly, carefully, and to really high standards, we can make dramatic savings, with huge benefits to people\u2019s lives.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We\u2019re using so much energy now that, as David Attenborough, the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.un.org\/press\/en\/2022\/sgsm21228.doc.htm\">UN<\/a> and others have shown, we\u2019re destroying a liveable planet. &nbsp;Our homes generate a massive chunk of CO2, and at the same time push people into fuel poverty.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"David Attenborough, People&#039;s Advocate for #COP26, Address to World Leaders | Climate Action\" width=\"1778\" height=\"1000\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/o7EpiXViSIQ?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>But cutting home energy use (by 80%+) we can help those most in need, cut bills, improve people\u2019s health and well-being, create high skilled local jobs, and help the planet at the same time.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Come along to the festival find out more\u2026<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The first day of <a href=\"https:\/\/civicsquare.notion.site\/Retrofit-Reimagined-9eb1d36585824faa89486ebfa12d1e86\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/civicsquare.notion.site\/Retrofit-Reimagined-9eb1d36585824faa89486ebfa12d1e86\">RETROFIT REIMAGINED <\/a>is at zero carbon house&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>103 Tindal Street, Birmingham B12 9QU.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>10 minute cycle from Birmingham city centre, or 20 minutes on No.50 bus.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Wednesday 13 July, 10am-6pm.&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Free admission.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Child-friendly.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ground floor wheelchair access.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Accessible wc.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Activities, presentations, displays, talks.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>All are welcome, but places are limited.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Please sign up here: <a href=\"https:\/\/t.co\/xDtDZiA4CM\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/t.co\/xDtDZiA4CM\">zerocarbonhouse open day registration form<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>All are warmly invited to RETROFIT REIMAGINED mini-festival in Birmingham, 13-16 July!&nbsp; zero carbon house is collaborating with: Civic Square,&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":4874,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[7],"tags":[16],"class_list":["post-4851","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-open-days","tag-open-day"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/zerocarbonhousebirmingham.org.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/4851"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/zerocarbonhousebirmingham.org.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/zerocarbonhousebirmingham.org.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/zerocarbonhousebirmingham.org.uk\/wp-json\/wp\